[{"category":"section","location":"api/#API","page":"API","text":"","title":"API"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#SpectralSuperpositions.AbstractSuperposition","page":"API","text":"Abstract type for creating 2-D spectra structs. The types and arguments have been defined as well as a validate_superposition function to ensure consistency.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SpectralSuperpositions.AbstractSuperposition"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#SpectralSuperpositions.AbstractSuperposition1D","page":"API","text":"Abstract type for creating 2-D spectra structs. The types and arguments have been defined as well as a validate_superposition function to ensure consistency.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SpectralSuperpositions.AbstractSuperposition1D"},{"category":"function","location":"api/#SpectralSuperpositions.axesinfo","page":"API","text":"axesinfo()\naxesinfo(s::Symbol)\naxesinfo(x)\n\nQuery the axis type and its physical dimensions.\n\nThere are 8 supported spectral-variable types, formed from the combinations of spatial/temporal domain, linear/angular geometry, and frequency/period quantity. There's one direction type :direction, for a total of 9 possible axis types.\n\naxesinfo() returns a dictionary with information for all 9 possible axis types.\naxesinfo(s::Symbol) returns information for a specific axis type, e.g. axesinfo(:wavenumber)\naxesinfo(x) return the axis information for the axes of a spectrum x.\n\nThe dictionary is as follows:\n\n:direction          => ((:direction,), 𝐀),\n:frequency          => ((:temporal, :linear, :frequency), 𝐓^-1),\n:angular_frequency  => ((:temporal, :angular, :frequency), 𝐀 * 𝐓^-1),\n:period             => ((:temporal, :linear, :period), 𝐓),\n:angular_period     => ((:temporal, :angular, :period), 𝐓 * 𝐀^-1),\n:wavenumber         => ((:spatial, :linear, :frequency), 𝐋^-1),\n:angular_wavenumber => ((:spatial, :angular, :frequency), 𝐀 * 𝐋^-1),\n:wavelength         => ((:spatial, :linear, :period), 𝐋),\n:angular_wavelength => ((:spatial, :angular, :period), 𝐋 * 𝐀^-1)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SpectralSuperpositions.axesinfo"},{"category":"function","location":"api/#SpectralSuperpositions.axesnames","page":"API","text":"axesnames(x::AbstractSuperposition)\naxesnames(x::AbstractSuperposition1D)\n\nReturn the axes names for an AbstractSuperposition or the axis name for an  AbstractSuperposition1D\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SpectralSuperpositions.axesnames"},{"category":"function","location":"api/#SpectralSuperpositions.axestypes","page":"API","text":"axestypes(x::Quantity)\naxestypes(x::Units)\naxestypes(x::AbstractVector{<:Quantity})\naxestypes(x::AbstractSuperposition)\naxestypes(x::AbstractSuperposition1D)\naxestypes(dim::Dimensions)\n\nReturns the type of axes as a symbol based on the unitful dimension. Uses the following  dictionary.\n\nDict{Unitful.Dimensions, Symbol} with 9 entries:\n𝐋⁻¹   => :wavenumber\n𝐀 𝐋⁻¹ => :angular_wavenumber\n𝐓⁻¹   => :frequency\n𝐀     => :direction\n𝐀 𝐓⁻¹ => :angular_frequency\n𝐋     => :wavelength\n𝐓     => :period\n𝐓 𝐀⁻¹ => :angular_period\n𝐋 𝐀⁻¹ => :angular_wavelength\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SpectralSuperpositions.axestypes"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#SpectralSuperpositions.coordinates-Tuple{AbstractSuperposition}","page":"API","text":"coordinates(x::AbstractSuperposition)\n\nReturns a symbol whether the Spectrum is in :polar or :cartesian coordinates. \n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SpectralSuperpositions.coordinates"},{"category":"function","location":"api/#SpectralSuperpositions.evenspacing","page":"API","text":"evenspacing(x::AbstractVector)\nevenspacing(x::AbstractSuperposition)\nevenspacing(x::AbstractSuperposition1D)\n\nReturn evenly spaced axis parameters as tuples (start, step, length).\n\nFor a Spectrum two such tuples are returned, one for each axis. Throws ArgumentError if the axis or axes are not evenly spaced.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SpectralSuperpositions.evenspacing"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#SpectralSuperpositions.isangular-Tuple{Any}","page":"API","text":"isangular(x)\n\nReturns true if the unit dimensions are :angular. \n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SpectralSuperpositions.isangular"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#SpectralSuperpositions.iscartesian-Tuple{AbstractSuperposition}","page":"API","text":"iscartesian(x::AbstractSuperposition)\n\nReturns true if the Spectrum is in :cartesian coordinates. \n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SpectralSuperpositions.iscartesian"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#SpectralSuperpositions.isdirection-Tuple{Any}","page":"API","text":"isdirection(x)\n\nReturns true if the unit dimensions are a :direction. \n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SpectralSuperpositions.isdirection"},{"category":"function","location":"api/#SpectralSuperpositions.isevenlyspaced","page":"API","text":"isevenlyspaced(x::AbstractVector)\nisevenlyspaced(x::AbstractSuperposition)\nisevenlyspaced(x::AbstractSuperposition1D)\n\nReturn true if the axis values are evenly spaced.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SpectralSuperpositions.isevenlyspaced"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#SpectralSuperpositions.isfrequency-Tuple{Any}","page":"API","text":"isfrequency(x)\n\nReturns true if the unit dimensions are :frequency. \n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SpectralSuperpositions.isfrequency"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#SpectralSuperpositions.islinear-Tuple{Any}","page":"API","text":"islinear(x)\n\nReturns true if the unit dimensions are :linear. \n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SpectralSuperpositions.islinear"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#SpectralSuperpositions.isperiod-Tuple{Any}","page":"API","text":"isperiod(x)\n\nReturns true if the unit dimensions are :period. \n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SpectralSuperpositions.isperiod"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#SpectralSuperpositions.ispolar-Tuple{AbstractSuperposition}","page":"API","text":"ispolar(x::AbstractSuperposition)\n\nReturns true if the Spectrum is in :polar coordinates. \n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SpectralSuperpositions.ispolar"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#SpectralSuperpositions.isspatial-Tuple{AbstractSuperposition}","page":"API","text":"isspatial(x::AbstractSuperposition)\n\nReturns true if the first axis of AbstractSuperposition has unit dimensions that are  :spatial. \n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SpectralSuperpositions.isspatial"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#SpectralSuperpositions.isspatial-Tuple{Any}","page":"API","text":"isspatial(x)\n\nReturns true if the unit dimensions are :spatial. \n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SpectralSuperpositions.isspatial"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#SpectralSuperpositions.isspectralvariable-Tuple{Any}","page":"API","text":"isspectralvariable(x)\n\nReturns true if the unit dimensions are not a direction and some other spectral variable  instead. \n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SpectralSuperpositions.isspectralvariable"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#SpectralSuperpositions.istemporal-Tuple{AbstractSuperposition}","page":"API","text":"istemporal(x::AbstractSuperposition)\n\nReturns true if the first axis of AbstractSuperposition has unit dimensions that are  :temporal. \n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SpectralSuperpositions.istemporal"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#SpectralSuperpositions.istemporal-Tuple{Any}","page":"API","text":"istemporal(x)\n\nReturns true if the unit dimensions are :temporal.\n\nSee also axesinfo()\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SpectralSuperpositions.istemporal"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Unitful.unit-Tuple{AbstractSuperposition, Symbol}","page":"API","text":"unit(x::AbstractSuperposition, quantity::Symbol)\nunit(x::AbstractSuperposition)\n\nExtend Unitful.unit for abstract superposition.\n\nThe quantity can be :axis (or the axis name) or :integral. These return the units of the spectral-variable axis, integral quantity, or the superposition data quantity. The default is quantity=:superposition.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Unitful.unit"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Unitful.unit-Tuple{AbstractSuperposition1D, Symbol}","page":"API","text":"unit(x::AbstractSuperposition1D, quantity::Symbol)\nunit(x::AbstractSuperposition1D)\n\nExtend Unitful.unit for abstract superposition.\n\nThe quantity can be :axis (or the axis name) or :integral. These return the units of the spectral-variable axis, integral quantity, or the superposition data quantity. The default is quantity=:superposition.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Unitful.unit"},{"category":"section","location":"#SpectralSuperpositions.jl","page":"Home","text":"Tiny placeholder documentation for the SpectralSuperpositions.jl package.","title":"SpectralSuperpositions.jl"},{"category":"section","location":"#Quick-Start","page":"Home","text":"This packages is meant to be used as a foundation for other frequency spectra packages.","title":"Quick Start"}]
